From 63d18a546120c2359ff7477067a30df928f00b9c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Naresh <ghostwriternr@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 3 Jun 2026 01:19:11 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] terminal_view: Add terminal launcher

Expose a small workspace-scoped terminal launcher for terminal agents
running inside Zed. The launcher accepts terminal.create requests over a
local Unix socket and opens a native terminal-panel tab in the originating
workspace.

The boundary is intentionally narrow: Zed owns display creation and the
environment contract that advertises the launcher socket and workspace
token. Agent clients such as Pi still own command execution, lifecycle,
output capture, waiting, and cancellation. This keeps Zed out of tmux or
agent-specific control semantics while giving terminal agents a native tab
for user-visible commands.

Store the launcher socket in a private tempfile directory, bound request
reads, and unregister workspace tokens when terminal panels are released.

